1
00:02:38,229 --> 00:02:40,830
She left without her shoes.

2
00:02:44,169 --> 00:02:46,340
She wasn't even wearing any shoes...

3
00:02:49,509 --> 00:02:50,740
when she was...

4
00:02:51,539 --> 00:02:52,639
going...

5
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,620
so far away.

6
00:03:26,210 --> 00:03:31,419
(Episode 4: I Won't Meet Anyone)

7
00:03:31,449 --> 00:03:36,719
(Episode 4: I Won't Meet Anyone)

8
00:03:39,990 --> 00:03:42,389
It's still dark outside
because the sun isn't up yet.

9
00:03:43,259 --> 00:03:45,129
Where does he wander
at this early hour?

10
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:49,300
He rarely leaves the penthouse,

11
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:53,500
but it looks like he goes
somewhere every morning.

12
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:58,280
I think he's obsessive
about repeating his morning routine.

13
00:03:59,039 --> 00:04:00,310
He takes a shower,

14
00:04:01,050 --> 00:04:02,150
cleans,

15
00:04:04,849 --> 00:04:06,080
sharpens his pencils,

16
00:04:09,919 --> 00:04:10,990
puts on some music,

17
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,159
and dances.

18
00:04:14,830 --> 00:04:15,830
What?

19
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:17,459
He dances?

20
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:06,509
What was that?
Was that a hallucination?

21
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:09,250
Am I still half asleep?

22
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:22,230
Good morning.

23
00:05:29,870 --> 00:05:31,069
Gosh.

24
00:05:37,079 --> 00:05:39,439
There's no way he was dancing.

25
00:05:40,079 --> 00:05:43,579
That cold psychopath
never even says hi back.

26
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,920
Did she see it?

27
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:51,689
Let's have lunch.

28
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:55,129
What will we be having today?
Will it be pork cutlets?

29
00:05:55,160 --> 00:05:56,189
- Hurry.
- Let's go.

30
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,800
It's yukgaejang today.

31
00:05:58,129 --> 00:06:00,870
- It's yukgaejang every day.
- I had it yesterday.

32
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:03,230
Should we eat out?

33
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:08,740
He never eats with his employees.

34
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:14,310
It seems like he does eat
by himself.

35
00:06:14,610 --> 00:06:18,319
Whatever he eats,
the kitchen is always cleaned up.

36
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,120
There's no smell, either.

37
00:06:20,620 --> 00:06:23,819
There must be some traces left.

38
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:27,730
I found it.

39
00:06:39,970 --> 00:06:41,439
Does it smell like kimchi?

40
00:06:41,769 --> 00:06:43,740
- Good work today.
- Good work, everyone.

41
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:45,610
- See you tomorrow.
- See you.

42
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:49,810
It's so cold these days.

43
00:06:50,009 --> 00:06:51,680
Wait for me.

44
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:58,290
After everyone leaves,

45
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:00,860
what does he do here all alone?

46
00:07:01,389 --> 00:07:04,060
Tomorrow morning,
he'll sneak out again...

47
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,399
like a cockroach.

48
00:07:20,680 --> 00:07:21,779
Here we go.

49
00:07:45,870 --> 00:07:47,040
He exercises?

50
00:07:56,350 --> 00:07:58,149
He's surprisingly good.

51
00:07:59,050 --> 00:08:02,290
I thought he was a loner
who never gets out.

52
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,990
Nice.

53
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,730
What a surprise!

54
00:08:12,759 --> 00:08:14,029
You're very good.

55
00:08:14,329 --> 00:08:15,730
It's so unexpected.

56
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,439
Why are you here?

57
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:18,870
I'm here to work out.

58
00:08:19,339 --> 00:08:20,910
Are you a member here, too?

59
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:23,139
It's so nice to see you here.

60
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,980
Are you leaving?

61
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:32,450
I actually want to learn how to
play squash. Can you teach me?

62
00:08:33,649 --> 00:08:35,389
Why are you ignoring me?

63
00:08:35,419 --> 00:08:37,919
I'm just happy to run into you.

64
00:08:40,289 --> 00:08:42,330
Isn't it about time
we became closer?

65
00:08:42,659 --> 00:08:44,059
Let's work out together...

66
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,899
and drink something cold
together later.

67
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,440
I work out alone.

68
00:08:58,779 --> 00:09:00,409
Of course you do.

69
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:12,889
Is it about Ms. Chae again?

70
00:09:14,629 --> 00:09:17,799
If she makes you that uncomfortable,
she'll have to go.

71
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,460
- I'll take her then.
- What?

72
00:09:20,669 --> 00:09:22,470
I want to teach her a lot.

73
00:09:22,570 --> 00:09:24,639
- I'll keep her near me and...
- You can't do that.

74
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,509
Why not?

75
00:09:29,710 --> 00:09:31,440
I'd like to...

76
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,340
kick her out of
the company for good.

77
00:09:34,509 --> 00:09:36,379
- If she stays here, she'll...
- What?

78
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:40,120
She'll get on my nerves.

79
00:09:41,549 --> 00:09:42,990
You can't fire someone
because of that.

80
00:09:43,090 --> 00:09:45,190
You know we can't fire
people that easily.

81
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:48,990
The ministry is keeping an eye on us
after the power abuse issue.

82
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,759
I'm sorry, Hwan Gi.

83
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:58,139
I'm sure she's been
sticking around you because of me.

84
00:09:58,740 --> 00:09:59,940
I told her to do that.

85
00:10:01,169 --> 00:10:03,409
It was an assignment
regarding the PI project.

86
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:06,009
I told her to analyze
what kind of person you are.

87
00:10:07,179 --> 00:10:10,919
She's observing whatever you do
with affection.

88
00:10:11,419 --> 00:10:15,149
Stop being so cold
and treat her nicely.

89
00:10:15,690 --> 00:10:16,789
With affection?

90
00:10:22,559 --> 00:10:24,360
Why is this so funny to me?

91
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:26,460
She's giving you such a hard time.

92
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,830
Eun Hwan Gi has met his
perfect match.

93
00:10:29,129 --> 00:10:32,470
It all starts from
hating each other.

94
00:10:33,100 --> 00:10:35,669
Give it some time, and tell me
if it's still too hard for you.

95
00:10:36,009 --> 00:10:37,809
I'll be more than happy to take her.

96
00:10:39,539 --> 00:10:41,879
No. She can stay with me.

97
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:48,389
What I mean is...

98
00:10:50,490 --> 00:10:52,259
What you mean is...

99
00:10:57,860 --> 00:11:00,100
We have no choice.
Just let her stay.

100
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:30,690
Mr. Kang.

101
00:11:31,299 --> 00:11:32,500
I'm here.

102
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:35,669
I've been waiting for you. Let's go.

103
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:58,690
They're together again.

104
00:11:59,289 --> 00:12:01,389
Where are they going together?

105
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,360
I've finished my assignment.

106
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:06,960
You have?

107
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,399
Where's your report paper?

108
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:12,100
I didn't have much to write about.

109
00:12:13,169 --> 00:12:14,309
Mr. Eun can be...

110
00:12:15,009 --> 00:12:17,139
defined with one word.

111
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:19,879
I'm all ears.

112
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,179
A cockroach.

113
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:24,379
A cockroach?

114
00:12:24,419 --> 00:12:27,419
Late at night, when everyone's
asleep and no one is watching,

115
00:12:27,549 --> 00:12:30,590
he becomes active.

116
00:12:30,919 --> 00:12:33,090
He's always dressed in back, too.

117
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,230
He's just like a cockroach.

118
00:12:36,929 --> 00:12:40,029
He never gives any instructions,

119
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,230
or hold any meetings.

120
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:45,669
He only spends the hard earned money
his employees make.

121
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:51,679
Silent Monster is like
an empty shell.

122
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:56,210
It's all just a show to pretend
the abusive boss has changed.

123
00:12:57,009 --> 00:12:58,250
That's harsh.

124
00:13:01,049 --> 00:13:02,789
All his employees are anxious.

125
00:13:03,720 --> 00:13:07,090
They wonder if it's really okay
to be doing nothing.

126
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:10,389
At least, you're working hard.

127
00:13:10,789 --> 00:13:12,899
I don't do much.

128
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:17,029
I just follow you around,
have good food,

129
00:13:17,330 --> 00:13:18,600
and meet people.

130
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:21,669
Do you think we meet people
just to have fun?

131
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:25,980
Giving presentations is
a big part of PR agencies' jobs.

132
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,879
It's, in essence, meeting people
and persuading them...

133
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:30,509
to get on our side.

134
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,350
I believe knowing a good person
is a lot more important than...

135
00:13:34,389 --> 00:13:37,450
reading a book both for your work
and for your life.

136
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:43,289
Today, an executive of
a major food company will be here.

137
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:45,299
For the 30th anniversary project
of Yong Ramyeon,

138
00:13:45,659 --> 00:13:47,159
there will be a bidding soon.

139
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,029
Do you understand what I mean?

140
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:53,399
Are we bribing him?

141
00:13:54,370 --> 00:13:57,070
We're just asking him to
let us enter the competition.

142
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,909
You'll soon figure it out,

143
00:14:00,240 --> 00:14:02,350
but they're not corrupt people.

144
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:09,250
Mr. Kang, you're already here.

145
00:14:09,289 --> 00:14:11,419
Hello, Managing Director Jin.

146
00:14:11,590 --> 00:14:13,090
Hello.

147
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:16,460
Who is this beauty?
Is she your girlfriend?

148
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,330
She's an employee
I think very highly of.

149
00:14:19,429 --> 00:14:20,730
She's my secret weapon.

150
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:25,100
I'm Chae Ro Woon.

151
00:14:25,139 --> 00:14:26,669
Nice to meet you.

152
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,610
Please take a seat.

153
00:14:29,070 --> 00:14:31,039
Sure. Let's sit down.

154
00:14:31,379 --> 00:14:34,509
He was supposed to
pass the ball to his team,

155
00:14:34,850 --> 00:14:37,149
but he ended up scoring an own goal.

156
00:14:37,179 --> 00:14:38,250
That's so funny.

157
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:40,679
We haven't even had any drink,

158
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:43,419
but this is so much fun.

159
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:44,519
Is it?

160
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:49,629
Do you know
what the secret to my success is?

161
00:14:49,659 --> 00:14:52,860
Your insight into the future?

162
00:14:52,899 --> 00:14:54,299
A global mindset?

163
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:55,929
You're going too far.

164
00:14:56,830 --> 00:15:00,169
The right answer is health.

165
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:01,870
Around my age,

166
00:15:01,909 --> 00:15:06,080
many of the competitors fall down...

167
00:15:06,279 --> 00:15:08,110
because of health issues.

168
00:15:08,309 --> 00:15:11,120
In addition to being competent,

169
00:15:11,279 --> 00:15:14,519
you're modest, too. My goodness.

170
00:15:20,919 --> 00:15:22,289
She's an employee
I think very highly of.

171
00:15:22,330 --> 00:15:24,230
I'm being recognized.

172
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,769
(New York Barbershop)

173
00:15:28,399 --> 00:15:29,769
She's my secret weapon.

174
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,470
Secret?

175
00:15:35,039 --> 00:15:37,169
My sister ended up dead...

176
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,110
at that company.

177
00:15:47,720 --> 00:15:48,820
(New York Barbershop)

178
00:15:49,389 --> 00:15:52,590
What will Dad say if he finds out?

179
00:15:55,759 --> 00:15:58,399
(Three years ago)

180
00:15:59,659 --> 00:16:02,129
- Gosh, it's so cold.
- Be careful, Mom.

181
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:07,039
Gosh, why are you
wearing those heels?

182
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:09,669
What happened to the pair
I bought at the department store?

183
00:16:11,740 --> 00:16:13,580
Those are too expensive.

184
00:16:13,610 --> 00:16:16,080
Who cares if they get a bit dirty?

185
00:16:16,649 --> 00:16:20,450
Your father used half of
the shoe polish on them yesterday.

186
00:16:20,519 --> 00:16:22,389
Even dirt will slide right off.

187
00:16:30,559 --> 00:16:32,129
Is your eldest...

188
00:16:32,230 --> 00:16:34,059
going to work at this hour?

189
00:16:34,129 --> 00:16:35,629
Yes, hello.

190
00:16:36,470 --> 00:16:39,899
She works for the best company
there is in the industry.

191
00:16:40,269 --> 00:16:41,940
She serves the big boss...

192
00:16:42,039 --> 00:16:44,580
at that amazing company.

193
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:46,909
Of course she is busy.

194
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:50,149
Just leave

195
00:16:50,309 --> 00:16:55,750
My life alone

196
00:16:56,289 --> 00:16:57,759
Do not

197
00:16:58,389 --> 00:17:00,860
- Get in my way
- That little...

198
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:03,029
- Mom.
- Anymore

199
00:17:03,929 --> 00:17:06,460
- I will live my way
- Gosh.

200
00:17:07,660 --> 00:17:09,829
Your youngest is just getting home.

201
00:17:11,099 --> 00:17:13,569
Are you all out waiting for me?

202
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,539
I'm so touched.

203
00:17:17,569 --> 00:17:19,809
- You punk. Look at the time.
- Mom.

204
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,579
Today,

205
00:17:22,380 --> 00:17:23,380
I...

206
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:25,920
Wait, it was yesterday.

207
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:30,390
I passed the audition yesterday.

208
00:17:31,049 --> 00:17:33,789
I was so happy.

209
00:17:35,259 --> 00:17:38,299
Guys, I'm going to be on a musical.

210
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:40,460
Will you come watch?

211
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,730
Are you the lead this time?

212
00:17:43,599 --> 00:17:45,799
I'll be a scene stealer...

213
00:17:46,039 --> 00:17:48,410
that walks all over
the lead character.

214
00:17:48,440 --> 00:17:50,740
I'll be playing 18 roles.

215
00:17:50,910 --> 00:17:54,380
That means
I'll play 18 different characters.

216
00:17:54,779 --> 00:17:59,079
You will be running in and out
of the stage.

217
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:01,650
It must be very hectic.

218
00:18:02,089 --> 00:18:03,089
That won't be all.

219
00:18:03,119 --> 00:18:06,289
She will be talking a lot.
It'll be so noisy.

220
00:18:07,359 --> 00:18:09,230
It's not just one or two.

221
00:18:09,390 --> 00:18:11,130
I'll play 18 roles.

222
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,970
Transformation complete.

223
00:18:15,769 --> 00:18:16,970
Gosh.

224
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:20,670
It's hard to believe
these two are sisters.

225
00:18:24,069 --> 00:18:25,079
My goodness.

226
00:18:27,039 --> 00:18:28,049
Oh, gosh.

227
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,609
Chae Ro Woon, those shoes...

228
00:18:31,279 --> 00:18:32,519
Aren't those your sister's?

229
00:18:32,549 --> 00:18:36,319
She lent them to me for good luck.

230
00:18:38,089 --> 00:18:40,089
Thank you, Ji Hye.

231
00:18:43,390 --> 00:18:46,630
After giving me great luck,

232
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,630
these shoes have died.

233
00:18:50,930 --> 00:18:53,440
Ro Woon, come over here.

234
00:18:53,569 --> 00:18:55,410
- Mom.
- Come over here.

235
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:58,039
- Come right here.
- Calm down.

236
00:19:00,210 --> 00:19:01,650
I'll buy her another pair.

237
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:03,980
I'll make money
and then buy her new ones.

238
00:19:04,109 --> 00:19:06,779
I'll buy her nicer
and prettier ones.

239
00:19:06,819 --> 00:19:09,650
- Look at her yapping.
- Mom.

240
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:11,559
- You better come over here.
- No.

241
00:19:12,059 --> 00:19:14,289
- She's going to get it today.
- Mom.

242
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:27,539
(New York Barbershop)

243
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,269
I wonder...

244
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,710
if Mom is watching me.

245
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:42,220
(New York Barbershop)

246
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:56,369
- Did you eat?
- Yes.

247
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:00,400
It was great.

248
00:20:02,569 --> 00:20:04,470
It was really delicious.

249
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:13,549
What's gotten into her?
Her answer got longer.

250
00:20:14,049 --> 00:20:15,950
Did something good happen?

251
00:20:16,190 --> 00:20:18,359
I bet she's drunk again.

252
00:20:18,390 --> 00:20:19,819
She looks fine to me.

253
00:20:20,559 --> 00:20:21,589
Gosh.

254
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:25,099
Ever since her sister died,

255
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:30,299
the cheerfulness in her also died.
She hardly talks now.

256
00:20:31,069 --> 00:20:34,000
Do you think
she'll start talking again?

257
00:20:50,019 --> 00:20:51,720
In one's life,

258
00:20:52,759 --> 00:20:55,059
some encounters are
imperatively necessary.

259
00:20:56,890 --> 00:20:58,559
On the other hand,
some are unnecessary,

260
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,559
I have an instruction...

261
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,269
to give.

262
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:08,740
- What's gotten into him?
- Are we getting yelled at?

263
00:21:08,869 --> 00:21:10,440
We're done for.

264
00:21:10,710 --> 00:21:12,380
I hope it's not a hassle.

265
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:16,779
What is it? Tell us, Boss.

266
00:21:24,859 --> 00:21:27,420
Do not meet anyone.

267
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:28,630
- Pardon?
- Pardon?

268
00:21:30,329 --> 00:21:31,759
What is he...

269
00:21:32,599 --> 00:21:34,099
Is this a series?

270
00:21:34,230 --> 00:21:36,269
It's the sequel to
"We won't say anything."

271
00:21:36,299 --> 00:21:38,200
"Do not meet anyone."

272
