273
00:21:49,210 --> 00:21:51,349
Does he think
I'll meet with the press?

274
00:21:51,579 --> 00:21:53,019
Is he suspicious of me?

275
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:57,920
Did he find out that I applied
for a different position?

276
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:01,289
Is he telling me to focus on work
instead of my family?

277
00:22:01,960 --> 00:22:02,960
My goodness.

278
00:22:04,329 --> 00:22:05,829
I'm not allowed to date
someone at the office?

279
00:22:06,599 --> 00:22:08,099
But I barely got started.

280
00:22:15,869 --> 00:22:17,609
(Managing Director Jin)

281
00:22:19,279 --> 00:22:20,710
Mr. Jin,

282
00:22:20,779 --> 00:22:22,380
did you get in all right last night?

283
00:22:23,380 --> 00:22:24,650
Yes.

284
00:22:25,079 --> 00:22:28,890
Of course. I'll run over
if you ask for me.

285
00:22:30,289 --> 00:22:33,589
Yes, sure.
I'll see you tomorrow then.

286
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:34,759
Bye.

287
00:22:34,890 --> 00:22:37,089
- My goodness.
- Who was that?

288
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,829
The person I met yesterday.

289
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:42,569
Exactly who are you meeting
all the time?

290
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:46,240
There will be a bidding for
Yong Ramyeon's anniversary project.

291
00:22:46,299 --> 00:22:47,599
The person in charge of PR...

292
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,940
Mr. Kang made you do
things like that?

293
00:22:50,910 --> 00:22:52,910
It wasn't anything weird.

294
00:22:52,980 --> 00:22:55,880
We had a 30-dollar-dinner.

295
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:57,549
We paid our own bills.

296
00:22:57,980 --> 00:23:02,150
Managing Director Jin loves sports,
so he doesn't even drink.

297
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:04,890
I noticed last time
that you play sports, too.

298
00:23:05,089 --> 00:23:06,789
Why don't you two play together?

299
00:23:06,890 --> 00:23:10,059
Instead of chasing people around,
do your work at your place.

300
00:23:10,589 --> 00:23:12,730
That way, you'll have 100 people
that know you,

301
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:15,529
instead of you knowing 100 people.

302
00:23:19,470 --> 00:23:20,470
But...

303
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:25,309
I don't know where my place is.

304
00:23:26,309 --> 00:23:28,779
I don't even know
what I should be doing.

305
00:23:29,910 --> 00:23:32,420
You never taught me anything.

306
00:23:40,119 --> 00:23:42,460
You'll come with me tomorrow, right?

307
00:23:43,059 --> 00:23:45,130
No. You shouldn't go either.

308
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,700
Don't be like that.

309
00:23:46,759 --> 00:23:49,500
- It's for the team. As a boss...
- Never.

310
00:23:51,299 --> 00:23:52,500
I don't want to go.

311
00:23:55,910 --> 00:23:57,569
I guess he really doesn't want to.

312
00:23:58,710 --> 00:24:01,210
If he hates it so much...

313
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,049
Yes, Mr. Jin.

314
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:10,150
About the meeting tomorrow...

315
00:24:10,549 --> 00:24:13,390
What do you think about going
early in the morning?

316
00:24:28,710 --> 00:24:30,509
Boss, you're here.

317
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:33,410
Managing Director Jin
is a member here as well.

318
00:24:35,779 --> 00:24:37,980
It looks like Silent Monster...

319
00:24:38,009 --> 00:24:40,880
is fated to work with Yong Ramyeon.
Don't you think?

320
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,650
What do you think you're...

321
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:50,460
I always wondered who came here
earlier than me.

322
00:24:50,589 --> 00:24:51,700
It was you.

323
00:24:53,029 --> 00:24:54,529
Let me introduce you.

324
00:24:55,069 --> 00:24:56,869
This is Managing Director Jin
of Yong Ramyeon.

325
00:24:57,569 --> 00:25:00,700
This is Silent Monster's boss,
Eun Hwan Gi.

326
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:04,339
Say hello.

327
00:25:05,779 --> 00:25:06,880
There you go.

328
00:25:07,509 --> 00:25:09,380
You should greet each other.

329
00:25:09,410 --> 00:25:10,410
Hello.

330
00:25:10,849 --> 00:25:13,619
Mr. Kang told me about you.

331
00:25:22,690 --> 00:25:24,859
It's nice and cool. Drink up.

332
00:25:25,230 --> 00:25:27,500
Okay, thank you. Right.

333
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,829
I heard you're
pretty good at squash.

334
00:25:29,869 --> 00:25:32,170
No, not really. I'm not good.

335
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:34,740
He's seriously so good.

336
00:25:34,769 --> 00:25:36,269
He's a pro.

337
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,740
Really?

338
00:25:39,309 --> 00:25:40,480
Let's play a game.

339
00:25:40,509 --> 00:25:44,549
I'm sorry. I like to exercise alone.

340
00:25:44,650 --> 00:25:48,019
Gosh, why? There's no fun in
playing against a wall by yourself.

341
00:25:48,119 --> 00:25:50,650
She's saying you're good. Teach me.

342
00:25:50,690 --> 00:25:52,559
When someone's looking at me...

343
00:25:53,289 --> 00:25:54,660
I always make mistakes.

344
00:25:54,690 --> 00:25:57,460
Mistakes? That's totally fine.

345
00:25:57,559 --> 00:25:59,059
Mistakes are what makes us human.

346
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:01,329
All right. Come on.
Let's play a game, okay?

347
00:26:03,869 --> 00:26:04,970
I'll take this.

348
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:09,640
Good.

349
00:26:10,339 --> 00:26:12,009
Here. Take this.

350
00:26:12,339 --> 00:26:13,779
I clearly said I don't
want to do this.

351
00:26:14,710 --> 00:26:17,910
I'll be a referee.

352
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:21,579
All right.

353
00:26:23,150 --> 00:26:25,259
Allow me to serve
since I'm older than you.

354
00:26:29,559 --> 00:26:31,490
What are you doing?
Why aren't you playing?

355
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:34,930
It's 1 to 0!

356
00:26:35,829 --> 00:26:37,569
Yes. Right.

357
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:39,599
Here we go.

358
00:26:48,609 --> 00:26:50,579
It's 2 to 0!

359
00:26:50,809 --> 00:26:52,980
What are you doing right now?
Do you think I'm a joke?

360
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,680
You don't even want to deal with me?

361
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:57,720
I think my staff was a bit
overly driven...

362
00:26:57,849 --> 00:27:00,259
to get Yong Ramyeon's
30th anniversary project.

363
00:27:01,259 --> 00:27:02,960
This is not how I get things done.

364
00:27:06,759 --> 00:27:08,059
What did you just say?

365
00:27:09,430 --> 00:27:12,900
I'll see you at the bidding
with our proposal.

366
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:14,299
Just a second.

367
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:17,740
I see that you're good
at making a fool out of people.

368
00:27:18,410 --> 00:27:21,509
Tell me. Did I ask you
to dance around in underwear for me?

369
00:27:21,609 --> 00:27:23,950
Or did I ask you for money?

370
00:27:24,150 --> 00:27:26,750
I just wanted to play
a game of squash with you.

371
00:27:28,279 --> 00:27:30,950
Definitely. My boss must've
misunderstood something.

372
00:27:31,089 --> 00:27:34,220
Did you misunderstand
my intentions, Ms. Chae?

373
00:27:34,460 --> 00:27:37,329
You asked me to come here
at this early hour.

374
00:27:37,359 --> 00:27:39,529
And why did you show up
with your boss?

375
00:27:39,599 --> 00:27:43,269
- Do you have a hidden agenda?
- Not at all.

376
00:27:43,299 --> 00:27:46,099
Then you hold this racquet...

377
00:27:46,140 --> 00:27:47,869
and tell this guy to leave!

378
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:50,869
Me?

379
00:27:51,410 --> 00:27:52,539
Let's go.

380
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:55,950
I've always wanted to learn
how to play squash.

381
00:27:55,980 --> 00:27:57,150
Will you teach me?

382
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:58,549
I'm a fast learner.

383
00:27:59,380 --> 00:28:00,779
Please give it to me. Thank you.

384
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:02,690
- Like this?
- All right. Yes.

385
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:05,420
Don't move your whole upper body
when you swing the racquet.

386
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:06,759
Hold it like this...

387
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:10,059
- and do this. That's it.
- Like this?

388
00:28:12,529 --> 00:28:14,529
All right. Let's play a game.

389
00:28:15,329 --> 00:28:17,099
What? You're still here?

390
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:18,700
Ro Woon, get out. I'll do it.

391
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:20,500
Swing the racquet like this.

392
00:28:21,269 --> 00:28:24,670
You're so stiff.
Relax your shoulders, okay? Good.

393
00:28:25,039 --> 00:28:26,279
All right, give it a try.

394
00:28:26,579 --> 00:28:28,240
You're so tense.

395
00:28:28,279 --> 00:28:29,680
You'll get hurt like this.

396
00:28:30,180 --> 00:28:31,819
All right. Relax your body first.

397
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:35,819
My gosh,
why is your upper body so mushy?

398
00:28:35,849 --> 00:28:37,390
I guess you don't
exercise your upper body.

399
00:28:37,420 --> 00:28:39,859
I mean, I saw how flexible
your legs are.

400
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:42,789
- Gosh, your body is so mushy...
- Please, Mr. Jin...

401
00:29:07,450 --> 00:29:08,849
I told you.

402
00:29:09,720 --> 00:29:11,349
I make mistakes
when someone is looking at me.

403
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:17,029
Boss.

404
00:29:31,009 --> 00:29:34,980
My gosh. I'm so sorry.
This might help relieve the pain...

405
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:41,019
I sincerely apologize. Are you...

406
00:29:43,089 --> 00:29:44,250
I'm going to sue him.

407
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:46,990
He obviously did it
intentionally to hurt me.

408
00:29:47,390 --> 00:29:48,789
I absolutely won't settle.

409
00:29:50,059 --> 00:29:52,730
Things just got a little intense
while you were exercising.

410
00:29:53,430 --> 00:29:54,599
What?

411
00:29:54,630 --> 00:29:57,000
Take a look at my CT and MRI
scans when they're out.

412
00:29:57,329 --> 00:29:59,000
It was definitely more
than "a little intense".

413
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,039
Please don't get so worked up.

414
00:30:03,140 --> 00:30:05,309
While collecting statements
about the incident,

415
00:30:06,309 --> 00:30:09,210
the fact that you were hitting on
our employee will be revealed.

416
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:12,319
What?

417
00:30:14,880 --> 00:30:17,619
My apologies.
I got a little worked up there.

418
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:19,289
She's an employee
I think very highly of.

419
00:30:19,319 --> 00:30:21,859
I take it that you don't want
to work with me.

420
00:30:22,430 --> 00:30:23,930
What are you talking about?

421
00:30:30,099 --> 00:30:31,269
This is for your hospital expenses.

422
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,009
Please forgive him,
and don't turn it into a big deal...

423
00:30:41,440 --> 00:30:42,809
for my sake.

424
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:00,900
What did he say?

425
00:31:01,299 --> 00:31:03,029
Does he not want us
to participate in the bidding?

426
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:06,170
I managed to get his permission
for the presentation.

427
00:31:08,369 --> 00:31:10,309
You didn't even do anything wrong,

428
00:31:10,809 --> 00:31:12,740
but you had to apologize to him.

429
00:31:13,609 --> 00:31:15,039
This is nothing.

430
00:31:15,549 --> 00:31:16,680
Let's go.

431
00:31:27,619 --> 00:31:28,859
I don't want to.

432
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:33,200
Hey, how can you say that when
I did all that work to sort it out?

433
00:31:35,970 --> 00:31:37,670
I don't want to work
with someone like that.

434
00:31:38,569 --> 00:31:39,839
I'm sorry to tell you this,

435
00:31:40,470 --> 00:31:42,809
but you're not in any position
to be picky at the moment.

436
00:31:43,109 --> 00:31:45,140
You should be asking companies
to work with you.

437
00:31:45,170 --> 00:31:46,880
He's obviously expecting
something more than that.

438
00:31:46,910 --> 00:31:49,380
He won't evaluate
our presentation fairly.

439
00:31:49,549 --> 00:31:51,480
Let's just give it a try.

440
00:31:51,609 --> 00:31:53,619
For our employees' sake. No.

441
00:31:54,480 --> 00:31:55,849
For my sake.

442
00:31:58,819 --> 00:32:00,119
There you go again.

443
00:32:02,930 --> 00:32:04,890
Cut him some slack for my sake.

444
00:32:05,089 --> 00:32:09,170
Ms. Kim, please hang in there
for my sake.

445
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:11,269
Please forgive him,
and don't turn it into a big deal...

446
00:32:11,829 --> 00:32:13,339
for my sake.

447
00:32:13,539 --> 00:32:14,869
"For my sake."

448
00:32:15,539 --> 00:32:17,970
He makes it sound like
he's sacrificing himself.

449
00:32:18,269 --> 00:32:19,839
Mr. Kang,
please look at this camera.

450
00:32:19,880 --> 00:32:23,309
But he's also unwittingly
expressing his desire for attention.

451
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,980
The right side of my face
looks better on camera.

452
00:32:26,019 --> 00:32:27,779
Please take photos
of my better side.

453
00:32:27,819 --> 00:32:29,920
I'm not saying enjoying
attention is bad.

454
00:32:30,319 --> 00:32:32,920
- What does Silent Monster mean?
- It's just that I'm not like him.

455
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:35,660
I've been wholeheartedly
thankful that he always...

456
00:32:36,259 --> 00:32:38,759
volunteers to be in the spotlight
on my behalf.

457
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,730
- We just took the first step,
- But...

458
00:32:40,759 --> 00:32:43,400
so please show us your support
and look forward to it.

459
00:32:43,430 --> 00:32:45,670
You once said that Mr. Eun
stays behind the scenes...

460
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:48,740
because you're more handsome
than him. Is that true?

461
00:32:50,940 --> 00:32:52,980
You haven't met
Mr. Eun in person, have you?

462
00:32:53,009 --> 00:32:54,009
- No.
- No.

463
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,450
If that's the case,
I can tell you in full confidence.

464
00:32:56,650 --> 00:32:59,950
I'm about 20 times
more handsome than him.

465
00:33:03,690 --> 00:33:06,289
So you're admitting that you're
better looking than him, right?

466
00:33:06,759 --> 00:33:09,829
The problem is that
he overly attracts attention...

467
00:33:11,559 --> 00:33:12,859
to the point that it's dangerous.

468
00:33:13,299 --> 00:33:15,000
Did you get any
plastic surgery done?

469
00:33:15,099 --> 00:33:16,769
- Pardon?
- Did you get any plastic surgery?

470
00:33:21,299 --> 00:33:25,039
Hey, what are you trying to say?

471
00:33:27,740 --> 00:33:30,910
Do you think I'm doing these things
because I want the attention?

472
00:33:31,650 --> 00:33:33,450
You're too greedy.

473
00:33:35,789 --> 00:33:37,690
That's hurtful and discouraging.

474
00:33:38,019 --> 00:33:40,089
I'm putting off what I have to do...

475
00:33:40,619 --> 00:33:43,259
to do my best
to help Silent Monster.

476
00:33:43,289 --> 00:33:44,390
I respect the way you do things,

477
00:33:44,430 --> 00:33:46,500
but I'm the one who's
in charge of Silent Monster.

478
00:33:47,200 --> 00:33:48,869
Take your hands off of this project.

479
00:33:50,500 --> 00:33:53,000
Hey, then what about our employees?

480
00:33:53,039 --> 00:33:54,569
I'll protect my own staff.

481
00:33:54,599 --> 00:33:55,869
How are you going to do that?

482
00:33:56,309 --> 00:33:59,839
By blowing our chance to
participate in the bidding?

483
00:34:00,109 --> 00:34:02,009
By wasting their time...

484
00:34:02,039 --> 00:34:03,609
when they should be learning
and building up experience?

485
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:07,619
Listen up.

486
00:34:07,650 --> 00:34:10,550
If you don't do this, no one will
give Silent Monster any work.

487
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:14,019
I know how competent you are,
but no one else does.

488
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:17,289
You don't want to play
dirty, petty tricks?

489
00:34:18,829 --> 00:34:20,260
I said I'll do them for you.

490
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:23,929
I'll do anything it takes
to get the ball rolling,

491
00:34:24,030 --> 00:34:25,269
so just do it your way...

492
00:34:25,300 --> 00:34:27,869
and show people what you can do.

493
00:34:28,199 --> 00:34:29,469
Does that sound good enough?

494
00:34:35,780 --> 00:34:37,679
Do you actually want to
protect your staff?

495
00:34:38,179 --> 00:34:39,719
Or are you just trying to
protect your pride?

496
00:34:42,219 --> 00:34:43,389
(Eun Hwan Gi)

497
00:35:24,030 --> 00:35:26,829
I'll protect my own staff.

498
00:35:29,130 --> 00:35:30,469
How are you going to do that?

499
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,239
By wasting their time...

500
00:35:33,269 --> 00:35:34,969
when they should be learning
and building up experience?

501
00:35:36,269 --> 00:35:37,739
Taking the bus and
getting a ride from me...

502
00:35:37,769 --> 00:35:40,539
- They're the same thing.
- Stop it.

503
00:35:41,210 --> 00:35:42,750
Are you late as well, Sun Bong?

504
00:35:44,380 --> 00:35:45,380
Yes.

505
00:35:45,650 --> 00:35:48,650
I went to a job interview
this morning.

506
00:35:48,889 --> 00:35:50,590
There is nothing to do
even if we come in early, anyway.

507
00:35:50,619 --> 00:35:51,690
I'll say.

508
00:35:52,289 --> 00:35:53,519
That's true.

509
00:35:54,159 --> 00:35:56,960
Yong Ramyeon's bidding is tomorrow.

510
00:35:57,329 --> 00:36:00,159
Everyone is busy finishing up
the presentation,

511
00:36:01,159 --> 00:36:03,730
- except for us.
- I'll say.

512
00:36:03,769 --> 00:36:05,269
There is nothing we can do.

513
00:36:05,429 --> 00:36:07,340
He doesn't share anything with us.

514
00:36:07,500 --> 00:36:08,539
I'll say.

515
00:36:09,070 --> 00:36:10,070
Let's go.

516
00:36:13,639 --> 00:36:16,010
Wait for me!

517
00:36:19,019 --> 00:36:20,619
Good morning.

518
00:36:22,849 --> 00:36:26,989
Am I not that late today?

519
00:36:27,159 --> 00:36:29,690
Or is everyone late?

520
00:36:29,730 --> 00:36:30,929
I'm on a diet.

521
00:36:54,550 --> 00:36:55,920
(The Korean ramyeon market...)

522
00:36:59,519 --> 00:37:01,090
(Spot the differences between the
old and new packagings)

523
00:37:12,539 --> 00:37:13,900
Are you late, too?

524
00:37:14,239 --> 00:37:16,909
I was on time, but...

525
00:37:17,010 --> 00:37:19,179
I had to go somewhere urgently.

526
00:37:19,239 --> 00:37:20,510
Do you have enteritis again?

