00:58:26,010 --> 00:58:28,780
I just had to memorize it
and do the presentation.

798
00:58:29,010 --> 00:58:32,949
It also had a surprisingly
heart-warming theme.

799
00:58:38,289 --> 00:58:41,059
To celebrate Yong Ramyeon's
30th anniversary,

800
00:58:41,119 --> 00:58:42,760
Silent Monster prepared...

801
00:58:42,820 --> 00:58:44,989
a social media photo contest.

802
00:58:45,760 --> 00:58:48,059
"Ramyeon That Doesn't Change".

803
00:58:48,500 --> 00:58:50,929
Yong Ramyeon has been there
for us for 30 years.

804
00:58:51,070 --> 00:58:53,030
Share the moments
you spent with Yong Ramyeon...

805
00:58:54,400 --> 00:58:55,400
with us.

806
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:56,500
Mom.

807
00:58:57,239 --> 00:58:58,369
I feel sick.

808
00:59:00,780 --> 00:59:02,639
Mom, my nose is runny.

809
00:59:02,780 --> 00:59:04,280
You can post a photo...

810
00:59:04,309 --> 00:59:06,550
- from your old photo album.
- Mom...

811
00:59:10,619 --> 00:59:12,550
Or you can reenact the moment...

812
00:59:13,019 --> 00:59:14,860
captured in one of your old photos.

813
00:59:14,889 --> 00:59:17,929
- Mom, I'm sick.
- Get some sleep now.

814
00:59:18,829 --> 00:59:20,829
Prepare for the presentation.

815
00:59:21,300 --> 00:59:23,730
Who are you referring to, Boss?

816
00:59:30,039 --> 00:59:31,909
Warm family affection.

817
00:59:31,940 --> 00:59:33,039
(AE Dang Yoo Hee)

818
00:59:33,710 --> 00:59:36,809
That strand of noodle
must be from her kid.

819
00:59:37,780 --> 00:59:39,750
Whenever she picks up snacks
for the team,

820
00:59:39,809 --> 00:59:43,920
she buys those old-school pastries
that we all used to eat growing up.

821
00:59:44,789 --> 00:59:47,690
She's the perfect person to express
the old-school sentimentality...

822
00:59:48,019 --> 00:59:49,860
this project is seeking.

823
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:52,989
Me?

824
00:59:53,929 --> 00:59:57,099
It'd been long since I
got actual work done.

825
00:59:57,130 --> 01:00:00,639
It made me think of when
I was single, and I was all excited.

826
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:04,010
After all,

827
01:00:05,369 --> 01:00:08,380
I'm just a mom
who picks up snacks for the team.

828
01:00:16,780 --> 01:00:19,619
No, I shouldn't even
call myself a mom.

829
01:00:20,559 --> 01:00:23,690
I didn't even take my kids to get
the flu shot on time,

830
01:00:23,730 --> 01:00:26,889
and I yelled at them
knowing that they're sick.

831
01:00:30,800 --> 01:00:31,969
I'm neither an employee...

832
01:00:33,099 --> 01:00:34,769
nor a mom.

833
01:00:37,510 --> 01:00:38,639
What am I?

834
01:00:55,289 --> 01:00:57,559
(Kang Woo Il)

835
01:01:04,800 --> 01:01:06,670
(Chae Ro Woon)

836
01:01:11,139 --> 01:01:12,469
(11 Missed Calls)

837
01:01:13,940 --> 01:01:15,739
Do you actually want to
protect your staff?

838
01:01:16,880 --> 01:01:18,010
(12 Missed Calls)

839
01:01:18,050 --> 01:01:19,380
(Chae Ro Woon)

840
01:01:19,949 --> 01:01:21,849
Or are you just trying
to protect your pride?

841
01:01:22,679 --> 01:01:24,289
(Chae Ro Woon)

842
01:01:33,690 --> 01:01:38,030
(Chae Ro Woon)

843
01:01:43,099 --> 01:01:44,739
- Hello?
- Are you...

844
01:01:45,440 --> 01:01:46,440
the boss?

845
01:01:47,239 --> 01:01:49,909
I have your staff members here.

846
01:01:51,110 --> 01:01:52,550
Get cash ready.

847
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:04,530
It's cold.

848
01:02:25,250 --> 01:02:26,409
It's 101 dollars.

849
01:02:27,420 --> 01:02:28,719
I'm sorry.

850
01:02:28,880 --> 01:02:32,320
The card reader is broken.
Please give me 101 dollars in cash.

851
01:02:38,530 --> 01:02:40,260
Another bottle of soju, please.

852
01:02:42,360 --> 01:02:44,300
I'm sorry.

853
01:03:09,019 --> 01:03:10,559
I want to drink more.

854
01:03:10,889 --> 01:03:12,159
I don't want to go home.

855
01:03:13,659 --> 01:03:14,760
It hurts.

856
01:03:18,199 --> 01:03:19,570
I don't want to get in.

857
01:03:21,039 --> 01:03:22,369
- I don't want to go home.
- Please go to Heukseok-dong.

858
01:03:22,400 --> 01:03:24,539
Areum Villa, Room 203.

859
01:03:24,869 --> 01:03:26,739
I don't want to go.

860
01:03:26,840 --> 01:03:30,039
Mister, drink with me.

861
01:03:31,650 --> 01:03:33,579
It's nice to meet you.

862
01:03:38,190 --> 01:03:39,320
What?

863
01:03:39,349 --> 01:03:42,389
When did you get all so
grown up, Son?

864
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:51,030
Room 907, Jinsang Apartment,
Myeonmok-dong.

865
01:03:52,199 --> 01:03:54,139
Come here! Where are you going?

866
01:03:54,769 --> 01:03:56,840
Son!

867
01:03:56,869 --> 01:03:58,809
Room 203, Secret Villa,
Bulgwang-dong.

868
01:03:58,840 --> 01:04:02,039
- Please drive carefully.
- Have a drink with me.

869
01:04:02,610 --> 01:04:04,480
- Bye.
- I can drink more.

870
01:04:04,610 --> 01:04:06,280
Let's drink.

871
01:04:08,519 --> 01:04:09,920
Drink with me.

872
01:04:10,690 --> 01:04:13,019
- I can still drink.
- Sir, excuse me.

873
01:04:15,260 --> 01:04:16,820
Let's go.

874
01:04:17,360 --> 01:04:19,389
Here we go.

875
01:04:19,429 --> 01:04:20,530
Let's go.

876
01:04:22,400 --> 01:04:25,769
Get up. Let's start walking.

877
01:04:26,500 --> 01:04:27,699
There you go.

878
01:04:28,900 --> 01:04:30,099
Here. Take it.

879
01:04:30,539 --> 01:04:32,539
Sir, please go to Hannam-dong.

880
01:04:32,639 --> 01:04:36,579
You're my girl.

881
01:04:58,300 --> 01:05:00,969
You said you're not
an easygoing person.

882
01:05:04,269 --> 01:05:06,309
What are you doing
at this shabby bar?

883
01:05:10,010 --> 01:05:13,050
You know
all your employees' addresses.

884
01:05:14,019 --> 01:05:15,449
Have you been watching us
the whole time?

885
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:18,219
Why?

886
01:05:18,989 --> 01:05:21,960
Why do you secretly
observe people from behind?

887
01:05:27,559 --> 01:05:29,960
Why are you never
in front of people?

888
01:05:37,769 --> 01:05:39,139
Is it because you can't?

889
01:05:42,179 --> 01:05:45,949
I thought you looked down on people.

890
01:05:48,050 --> 01:05:49,179
Are you...

891
01:05:51,019 --> 01:05:52,289
scared of people?

892
01:05:55,690 --> 01:05:57,559
When people stare at you,

893
01:05:58,329 --> 01:06:02,230
do you make mistakes or something?

894
01:06:07,869 --> 01:06:12,570
I know people like you very well.

895
01:06:14,539 --> 01:06:16,739
You hide where there's no one else.

896
01:06:17,409 --> 01:06:20,510
You quietly keep your place.

897
01:06:24,420 --> 01:06:26,789
Someone in my family is like that.

898
01:06:28,519 --> 01:06:29,690
No.

899
01:06:30,659 --> 01:06:32,090
Apart from me,

900
01:06:32,960 --> 01:06:35,360
everyone in my family is like that.

901
01:06:37,469 --> 01:06:38,630
Dad,

902
01:06:40,099 --> 01:06:41,340
Mom,

903
01:06:44,239 --> 01:06:45,739
and my sister.

904
01:06:54,250 --> 01:06:58,219
But let alone a hundred people,

905
01:06:59,119 --> 01:07:01,519
not a single person noticed.

906
01:07:03,190 --> 01:07:06,159
If you just stand there and watch,

907
01:07:07,960 --> 01:07:10,159
nothing will happen.

908
01:07:17,739 --> 01:07:19,570
Just by watching,

909
01:07:22,710 --> 01:07:24,780
you can't protect anyone.

910
01:08:29,140 --> 01:08:32,010
(My Shy Boss)

911
01:08:32,479 --> 01:08:34,220
It felt warm.

912
01:08:34,250 --> 01:08:36,449
I said I'm sorry.

913
01:08:36,479 --> 01:08:38,649
- I'm the one who should say that.
- He held you in his arms?

914
01:08:38,689 --> 01:08:40,350
I just vaguely remember the smell.

915
01:08:40,390 --> 01:08:41,659
It smelled like peppermint candy.

916
01:08:41,689 --> 01:08:45,029
What Silent Monster needs right now
is not work, but teamwork.

917
01:08:45,060 --> 01:08:46,729
Why don't we have a workshop
to build up teamwork?

918
01:08:46,760 --> 01:08:48,560
Will it be an overnight trip?

919
01:08:48,600 --> 01:08:50,260
Why doesn't he tell people
that he's engaged?

920
01:08:50,300 --> 01:08:51,569
Are you stopping him
from doing that, too?

921
01:08:51,670 --> 01:08:53,869
I can never lie to you.

922
01:08:53,899 --> 01:08:55,539
A video clip?

923
01:08:55,569 --> 01:08:57,069
I really don't understand
what you're talking about.

924
01:08:57,710 --> 01:08:59,170
- What are you watching?
- He's not saying anything.

925
01:08:59,210 --> 01:09:00,539
Is that Mr. Eun?

926
01:09:00,569 --> 01:09:03,710
I'll try to make Mr. Eun
become like Mr. Kang.

927
01:09:03,739 --> 01:09:06,409
That's absurd. It'll be impossible.

928
01:09:06,449 --> 01:09:08,149
I'm sure Hwan Gi will change.

929
01:09:08,250 --> 01:09:09,380
He's capable of doing that.

930
01:09:09,720 --> 01:09:13,119
I hope this workshop will
help Hwan Gi change.
